cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about developing a new method for finding video CNN architectures that capture rich spatio-temporal information in videos. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also introduces a novel evolutionary search algorithm that automatically explores models with different types and combinations of layers to jointly learn interactions between spatial and temporal aspects of video representations, which falls under the category of cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper proposes a new component, the iTGM layer, which is a type of neural network layer, and thus, the paper could also be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). The paper also evaluates its proposed method on multiple datasets, including HMDB, Kinetics, and Moments in Time, which are related to multimedia and video analysis, and thus, the paper could also be categorized under cs.MM (Multimedia). Finally, the paper uses an evolutionary algorithm to optimize the neural architectures, which falls under the category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
